    >
      ‚Üì
    </button>
  </section>
  <section class="card content-block" id="scroll-target">
    <h2>A slight pivot</h2>
    <p>
      After numerous rounds of iterative design based on the established group
      model, the organisation made a methodological shift. The Consultant‚Äôs role
      moved from structured, one-to-one support, to a more facilitative
      group-led format.
    </p>

    <p>
      To understand the implications I observed the roll-out training, and
      attended a number of groups to see how the new format was landing in
      practice.
    </p>

    <p>
      The tool needed to adapt to support a different group dynamic. Rather than
      discarding the exsiting work I adpated. I introduced an index layer in
      front of the existing screens ‚Äî a stripped-back overview of all members
      that supported dynamic facilitation while preserving access to depth when
      needed.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="card content-block">
    <h2>Impact & reflections</h2>
    <p>
      This was a challenging project for a number of reasons, not least of which
      the emotional attachment felt at the highest levels of the business
      coupled with a change of direction mid-way through.
    </p>

    <p>
      Thgeorugh consistent stakeholder collaboration and user research, I was
      able to successfully design an early beta that played a notable part in
      <strong> qulity of service improvments</strong>, and navigate a path
      through numerous iterations, conflicting opinions and the business leads
      inherent urge to take a kitchen sink approach, to poduce a design that was
      test and proven, derisking development.
    </p>
  </section>
